{
  "final_answer": "## Segment-Level FCF Proxy Analysis (Q1 2026)\n\nAll figures are in **millions of dollars** and reflect the recast consolidated entity (SpaceX + xAI + X Holdings under common-control accounting).\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Retrieve Q1 2026 Segment Data\n\n| Metric | Space | Connectivity | AI |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|\n| **Segment Adjusted EBITDA** | $(351) | $2,087 | $(609) |\n| **Capital Expenditures** | $1,052 | $1,332 | $7,723 |\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Calculate FCF Proxy (Adj. EBITDA − Capex)\n\n| Segment | Q1 2026 FCF Proxy | Annualized (×4) |\n|---|---:|---:|\n| **Space** | −$1,403 | −$5,612 |\n| **Connectivity** | **$755** | **$3,020** |\n| **AI** | −$8,332 | −$33,328 |\n\n**Calculations:**\n- Space: −$351 − $1,052 = **−$1,403M**\n- Connectivity: $2,087 − $1,332 = **$755M**\n- AI: −$609 − $7,723 = **−$8,332M**\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: How Many Years of Connectivity Annualized FCF Proxy Fund One Year of AI Capex?\n\n| Component | Value |\n|---|---:|\n| AI capex at Q1 2026 run-rate (annualized) | $7,723 × 4 = **$30,892M** |\n| Connectivity FCF proxy at Q1 2026 run-rate (annualized) | $755 × 4 = **$3,020M** |\n\n$$\\text{Years} = \\frac{\\$30{,}892\\text{M}}{\\$3{,}020\\text{M}} \\approx \\boxed{10.23 \\text{ years}}$$\n\n---\n\n### Interpretation\n\nAt Q1 2026 run-rates, it would take approximately **10.2 years** of Connectivity's annualized free cash flow generation (the only segment with positive FCF proxy) to fund a single year of AI segment capital expenditures. This underscores the massive capital intensity of the AI/data center buildout relative to the company's current cash-generating capacity — the AI segment alone consumed over 76% of total Q1 2026 capex ($7.7B of $10.1B), while Connectivity was the sole segment producing a positive FCF proxy.\n\n**Sources:**\n- SpaceX S-1 Filing (May 20, 2026): https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm",
